China imposes embargo on N. Korea vessels in strict sanction
YINGKOU, China--In response to Pyongyang’s nuclear and missile tests, China has banned the entry of North Korean vessels to Yingkou port in Liaoning province, a major gateway for China’s coal imports from the reclusive state.
